info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 20 at 2:20PM MST until February 22 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Tucson
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TO 8 PM MST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to near 50 mph expected. Areas of blowing dust with reduced visibilities possible. * WHERE...Western Pima County, Tohono O`odham Nation, South Central Pinal County and Upper Gila River Valley. * WHEN...From 5 AM to 8 PM MST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. Blow dust with reduced visibilities could result in difficult travel conditions in dust prone areas. &&
